Anne,<br><br>
Thanks for your kind words of encouragement. It has been a rough day of sorts. <br><br>
MTF speaks of the medicine wheel, a very powerful and important metaphor to describe what it is to be very human. The wheel is connected across most cultures, and comes through from what can best be described as the beginning time. Whether it be the Great Spirit of Native American Cultures or 'Neter', the Ancient Egyptian progenator Supreme Being, all the wheels represents the order and flow of life as determined by the 'One in Charge'. <br><br>
I am giving serious thought to the Medicine Wheel, and I find that I am in part at each of its four points simultaneously. I guess that is how I have learned to cope with some of the problems that bounce around my head. The wheel is a continuum, and it is life. I am beginning to trust life, for without that, there can be no trust of anything. <br><br>
All this may seem obscure to some, but it is the process I must use to regain that which I lost so long ago in Vietnam.<br><br>
What makes this experience bearable is the understanding.<br><br>
Art    
